Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!). Pop the potatoes on a #low sided wide baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, scatter over half the @North Indian Style Spice Mix{1%portion} and half the @mustard seeds{1%portion} then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out. Once your oven is hot, roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Pop the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} into a #small bowl{} with the remaining North Indian spice mix. Add a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} then season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix together.

Line a #baking tray{} with #baking paper{}. Pat the @hake fillets{2} dry with some #kitchen roll{} and season both sides with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Lay them on the baking paper. Spread half the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} on the top and sides of the hake pieces (we'll use the rest later), then spoon over the crumb. Push it down to ensure it sticks (don't worry if some of it falls off).

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw fish!

Zest the @lime{1/2}(zested) and cut into wedges. Trim the @green beans{150%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Pop the remaining mayonnaise into a small bowl with the lime zest. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir together.

About ~{10%minutes} before the potatoes are ready, roast the fish on the middle shelf of your oven until the crumbs are golden and the fish is cooked, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The hake is cooked when opaque all the way through.

While everything cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} over medium high heat. Once hot, add the green beans and stir fry for ~{2%minutes} then add the garlic and remaining mustard seeds, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir fry for ~{1%minute} then add a splash of @water{splash}, cover with a #lid{} (or some #foil{}) and steam fry until tender, ~{2-3%minutes}. Divide the fish, potatoes and green beans between plates. Serve with the limey mayo and lime wedges alongside for squeezing over. Enjoy!